<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9233> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9233" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 744, footnote 203" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7447> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7447" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See MRR 2.71. For discussions of his origin and command, see Wiseman, NM 210, no. 13. In MRR, for see below, Pontifices, read see below, note 8. On his name, see Shackleton Bailey, Studies 7. He is almost certainly the later Pontifex Minor (MRR 2.135, 137, note 12; and Shackleton Bailey, loc. cit.).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5119> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5119" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See L. R. Taylor, \"Caesar's Colleagues in the Pontifical College,\" AJPh 63 (1942) 385-412; and above, 73, 69, 63, 60, and 58, Pontifices." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4623> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4623" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The following persons, named in a list in Macrobius (Sat. 3.13.11) appear to have entered the college of Pontifices after Caesar was inaugurated in 73 and before P. Sulpicius Galba, who entered at the latest in 69 (see L. R. Taylor, AJPh 63 [1942] 385-412):" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4172> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4172" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. An officer under Norbanus who treacherously murdered other officers of Norbanus and Papirius Carbo at a banquet and surrendered Ariminum to Metellus (App. BC 1.91; Ps.-Ascon. 234 Stangl). See below, Pontifices." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4171> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4171" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "8 For the praenomen, see App. BC 1.60. Possibly the P. Albinovanus who was a Pontifex Minor from before 69 to 57 or after (Macrob. Sat. 3.13. 11; Cic. Har. Resp. 12). See L. R. Taylor, AJPh 63 (1942) 385ff." .
